Two Fukushima Workers Taken to Hospital After Being Exposed to Radiation

-- B y   G e a r o i d   R e i d y
-- 
2011-03-24T06:52:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/two-fukushima-workers-taken-to-hospital-after-being-exposed-to-radiation.html
Three workers at Tokyo Electric
Power Co.’s Fukushima Dai-Ichi No. 3 reactor were exposed to
radiation and two were taken to the hospital,  Japan ’s nuclear
safety agency said.  The workers were irradiated at levels between 170 and 180
millisieverts per hour while laying a cable, Hidehiko Nishiyama,
a spokesman for the agency, said today. The incident occurred
around 12:09 p.m. local time today, Nishiyama said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gearoid Reidy in Tokyo at 
